.TH UPGRADE-ALPINE 1 "December 2025" "distup 1.2.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
upgrade-alpine \- upgrade Alpine Linux to stable or edge
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B upgrade-alpine
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] [\fBstable\fR|\fBedge\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B upgrade-alpine
upgrades Alpine Linux systems to the latest stable release or Edge
(rolling release) branch.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-dry\-run
Show what would be done without making any changes.
.TP
.B \-\-version\fR, \fB\-V
Show version information.
.TP
.B \-\-help\fR, \fB\-h
Show help message.
.SH MODES
.TP
.B stable
Upgrade to latest stable Alpine release.
.TP
.B edge
Switch to Edge rolling release branch.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/apk/repositories
Repository configuration (backed up before modification).
.TP
.I /var/log/upgrade-alpine-*.log
Log file containing detailed upgrade output.
